%I A391775 #57 Apr 03 2026 10:08:49
%S A391775 1125,10512,15125,235125,946125,1781725,6670125
%N A391775 Discriminants of totally real quartic fields in which every additively indecomposable element is a unit.
%C A391775 For any totally real field K, an additively indecomposable element of K is a totally positive element in the maximal order of K which cannot be written as the sum of two totally positive integral elements of K.  Here, an element x of K is totally positive if all conjugates of x are positive real numbers. Any totally positive unit is additively indecomposable, although the converse need not hold.
%C A391775 Term a(8) is greater than 10^7.  Further terms of this sequence include 88073725 (from Q(sqrt(2523 + 754*sqrt(5)))), 2183005125 (from Q(sqrt(20895 + 8358*sqrt(5)))), and 703556316125 (from Q(sqrt(375115 + 150046*sqrt(5)))).
%C A391775 It is an open problem whether this sequence has infinitely many terms.  All known terms correspond to totally real quartic fields of the form Q(sqrt(A + B*sqrt(D))) with D = 3 or 5.  A special case of a conjecture of Siu Hang Man [Man 2024, Conjecture 1.7] states that there are only finitely many real biquadratic fields in which every additively indecomposable element is a unit.
%H A391775 Martin Čech, Dominik Lachman, Josef Svoboda, Magdaléna Tinková, and Kristýna Zemková, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/mana.201800109">Universal quadratic forms and indecomposables over biquadratic fields</a>, Math. Nachr. 292 (2019), no. 3, 540-555.
%H A391775 Siu Hang Man, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aim.2024.109694">Minimal rank of universal lattices and number of indecomposable elements in real multiquadratic fields</a>, Adv. Math. 447 (2024), Paper No. 109694, 38 pp.
%H A391775 Magdaléna Tinková, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0013091525000112">Bounds on the Pythagoras number and indecomposables in biquadratic fields</a>, Proc. Edinb. Math. Soc. (2) 68 (2025), no. 3, 843-868.
%H A391775 Robin Visser, <a href="https://github.com/rvisser7/indecomposables">Database of indecomposable elements over number fields</a>, 2026.
%e A391775 a(1) = 1125, as the maximal real subfield K of the cyclotomic field Q(zeta_15) is a totally real quartic field of discriminant 1125 and all additively indecomposable elements of K are units.
%e A391775 The first seven terms arise as discriminants of the following totally real quartic fields:
%e A391775   a(1) = 1125: Q(sqrt(15 + 6*sqrt(5))),
%e A391775   a(2) = 10512: Q(sqrt(11 + 4*sqrt(3))),
%e A391775   a(3) = 15125: Q(sqrt(55 + 22*sqrt(5))),
%e A391775   a(4) = 235125: Q(sqrt(135 + 42*sqrt(5))),
%e A391775   a(5) = 946125: Q(sqrt(435 + 174*sqrt(5))),
%e A391775   a(6) = 1781725: Q(sqrt(363 + 110*sqrt(5))),
%e A391775   a(7) = 6670125: Q(sqrt(1155 + 462*sqrt(5))).
%Y A391775 Cf. A387203, A387207, A387574, A387575, A389888.
